AboutUseFirstParagraph.translation: Regobs uses cookies to improve your user experience when you visit the website. A cookie is a text file that, when visiting or interacting with a website, is placed in your browser's internal memory.

AboutUseSecondParagraph.translation: The basis for this is Article 6 (1) (f) of the Privacy Policy, which allows us to process information that is necessary to safeguard an interest that outweighs the individual's privacy. That interest is to make our website work well so that you get a good user experience.

AboutUseThirdParagraph.translation: Regobs does not use cookies to map individual users' usage patterns or other information that may violate their privacy.

CookiesDescription.translation: In the table below we list which cookies beta.regobs.no uses, which data is stored and why the site needs them.

CustomizeDescription.translation: Most modern browsers (Google Chrome, Internet Explorer, Firefox, Safari, Opera, etc.) are set to automatically accept cookies, but you can choose to change your settings so that cookies are not accepted. We note that this could lead to regobs.no not working optimally.
